  "number": 1967,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/1967",
  "title": "fix(Configure): use props a unique source of truth",
  "body": "With this PR I removed the fact that we can read `<Configure>` parameters from the search state, as it's not easy to handle if we also provide a way to change them directly from the props. \r\n\r\nThe props passed through `Configure` will only be pushed to search state. If the parameters needs to be modified, then the props of `Configure` needs to be modified. It means that when reading from a url, then the configure parameters must be extracted and passed through the props. \r\n\r\nIf three params where passed to the `Configure` at the first rendering, and then as the second one only two props are passed, then the third one will disappear from the `search state`. ",
